metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Hollywood Nights has complexity on par with the typical song, having near-average scores in Melodic Complexity and Chord-Melody Tension and below-average scores in Chord Complexity, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Hollywood Nights is written in the key of E Mixolydian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 2nd most popular key among Mixolydian keys and     the 26th most popular  among all keys. The E Mixolydian scale is similar to the E Major scale except that its 7th note (D) is a half step lower.  Mixolydian chord progressions are heavily featured in many genres of music like classic rock, which relies on the major chord built on the 7th scale degree. 

See the E Mixolydian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: This is a great song that uses the popular I-IV-V chords.  The bass line actually pedals on the low E note while the chords change.  Some of the notes are sung as triplets which can't be notated as of yet in Hookpad so I did my best to get as close as I can.
